Name: UnguardedReturn

Synopsis: A return statement occurs outside a function body.

Syntax:

Types:

Function:
       
Usage:

Details:

Description:
A [Rascal:Return] statement is used to return a value from a function.
It is an error to use it outside a function body.

Examples:
<screen>
int triple(int n) { return 3 * n; }
triple(5);
</screen>
Using return outside a function body gives an error:
<screen warning>
return 3;
</screen>
